LEGAL CASE ANALYSIS REPORT

Case Number: FIR No. 184/2025
Estimated Duration: 2 years

CASE DETAILS
The complainant alleges deliberate damage to her car by the accused following a heated argument regarding parking. CCTV evidence supports her claims, showing the accused in the vicinity.

IMPORTANT POINTS
Car damaged deliberately by the accused.
- CCTV footage shows the accused near the complainant's car on the incident day.
- Argument between complainant and accused prior to the incident.

SECTIONS INVOLVED
IPC Section 427 - Mischief causing damage
- IPC Section 504 - Intentional insult with intent to provoke breach of peace
- IPC Section 506 - Criminal intimidation

DEFENSE SECTIONS
IPC Section 77 - Act done in good faith regarding a private right

DEFENSE STRATEGY
Establish lack of intention to commit damage; argue that any actions taken were in self-defense or due to provocation.

PERSONS INVOLVED
Mrs. Kavitha Narayanan (Complainant)
- Mr. Vignesh Raja (Accused)
- SI Meenakshi Sundaram (Investigating Officer)
- Mr. Arul Mani (Witness)
- Mrs. Priyanka Devi (Witness)
- Mr. Harish Kumar (Witness)